[+] Build
Boost must be installed in your home directory to be able do use the Makefile
Then do a
$ make p1
                                          
[+] Vizualization of the graphs
Install graphviz (http://www.graphviz.org/) 
Then for the random graph generated in p3.cpp for instance run
$ dot randomgraph.dot -Tps -o randomgraph.ps

[+] Linking problem
Please try to compile the boost example and let me know if it works for you
$ g++ -I ~/boost/ -c read_graphviz.cpp
$ g++ read_graphviz.o ~/boost/stage/lib/libboost_graph.a

-Damien
